<br>
First thing about pet control:  Group early in your character's life...  Soloing can be fun and better, but you won't learn the first thing about pet control if you do.  I will usually try to get a group and solo until I get one...<br>
<br>
I saw it mentioned (not sure by who) that they don't use the assist command and rather they use the pointer to target.  I will use the assist command, but I won't send in the pet until I see the mob's hps go down to at least 80%.<br>
This has saved me a lot of trouble.<br>
<br>
The only other thing that I feel is good for pet control besides what was mentioned in other posts, is if you make a mistake, own up to it.  A lot of people that complain about this mage or that mage, have been in a group with a mage who had poor pet control and wouldn't own up to their mistakes.  I would rather own up to my mistakes and learn from them, then sit there and not take the blame...   Because of this, I don't have a bad name on my server.  When I say, &quot;It wasn't my fault this time,  I was assisting the main tank, and it wasn't my pet that broke the mez&quot;, my groups will tell the chanter to listen to me because I will own up for my mistakes.<br>
<br>
Just my opinion on things.  <br>
