<br>
Earthen boots (or DE /hide ability)<br>
Focus item (if u have to get rid of pet might as well get mana for it)<br>
The ability to type /pet get lost fast (if your casting u cant use above)<br>
<br>
If you dont have all the above dont group.<br>
<br>
There is allot more to pet control but ive seen here or in other threads..just thought i would add these things.<br>
<br>
Yes paying attention is an important aspect..but also knowing when to cast spells like nukes etc is as well.  U cant use pet control buttons, EB or Focus if your nuking or casting.<br>
<br>
Also if sometimes u may get hit by a mob u dont see or your trained or something pops right on top of u...if the mob isnt single its probably best to focus the pet away really fast so the chanter can mez and the tank can chose the mob he wants to kill instead of you pet dictating the fight.<br>
<br>
/sigh<br>
<br>
So many subtle aspects of pet control its hard not to wright a book on it.  Just keep in mind even if you group from 1 to 50..u still can learn more.  Also at the 50+ level when if you mess up the chanter dies and if this happens we all die, its easy to learn some new tricks.<br>
<br>
btw doesnt matter how bad pathing is you can always use a pet...the question is..is it worth it?  Ie u can use a pet in hate however u will be constantly watching pet..sometimes not sending it in, you cant cast anything (ie u cant use buttons yada yada yada) and you will go thru like a hundred pets before u know it.  Not to mention a mage in hate gives people a heart attack when they summon pets(if they dont know u that is).  However, if u dont use pets in hate...it still should be memmed since its a great spell to cast during potential wipeouts and clerics are camping.  Earth pet can tank mobs for a bit giving time for cleric to camp...however air pet is best for those clerics of innoruk who want to heal everything.<br>
<br>
