<br>
If you're malising mobs (as I was doing last night in a CC Queen group) you sometimes get resists.  Make a hotkey like this:<br>
<br>
/g MALISE LANDED - %T resists decreased<br>
<br>
Press this if you get the 'your target looks uncomfortable' message because,<br>
<br>
1) Its easy for group members to lose this in battle spam<br>
2) Everyone but magicians and shamen (who also have the same line of spells) will not know what this means.  Adding the description really helps the group. <p>Edano<br>
Lanys T`Vyl</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uxumten.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Xumten</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#333333>(3/21/01 3:21:25 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerlibrarysubmissions.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=35.topic&index=30>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Mages who brag about controling their pet</span><hr size=1> Nonhealer I really have to advise not to use a hotkey for your spouse that has /assist and /pet attack in same key. Really should have two seperate keys for that. It will cause problems. <br>
<br>
But to answer the original question. I dont brag that I have good pet control. I more or less feel that I dont have BAD pet control. Like a nuke for a wizzy, a sword for a warrior -- pets are our weapons. The big difference is that if we dont know how to use it we can get entire parties killed. If a wizzy cant control his burning he just gets himself killed. <br>
<br>
SIMMAH DOWN NAH!<br>
<br>
I just learned not to be so darn eager to send Jobn in. If your dealing with Chanters/Multiple Pulls then be patient. #1 rule -- Wait for the MOBs to get mezzed before you do ANYTHING. Once they are mezzd target tank -- throw a DS on your him(since he has waiting line for his loving now). Now hit /assist and Mala the MOB. Mala doesnt break Mez so you can VISUALLY see that you hit the right MOB. Now send in Jobn. In this case you have gotten DS and Mala out of the way and have given the Tank plenty of time to aquire the target and get a good assist off of him.<br>
<br>
And when it comes to indoor grouping... I tell my pet to back off when MOB gets down to about 25 - 30% health -- back it off before it turns and runs. Let the tanks go chasing. Due to pathing and such your &quot;command distance&quot; can be SEVERLY handicapped indoors. <br>
<br>
